Class RoomEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • RoomEntry

    public class RoomEntry
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<RoomEntry>
    This class is part of the Maze project. It represents the single Room of a maze.

      • outOfRange

        public boolean outOfRange​(int negative)
        RoomEntry's can have opening doors to the entrance of the maze or the exit of the maze, however these out of range ids can not be graph-wise accessed since they don't exist. This method sets the door states as if they do, but don't add a RoomEntry object to its list of accessible rooms.
        Parameters:
        negative - the out of range id which is for drawing purposes
        Returns:
        whether or not it is valid to add into out of range rooms

      • draw

        public void draw​(java.awt.Graphics2D g,
                 int offset)
        Draws this current RoomEntry as part of the overall maze and/or solution path. This uses offsets based on its position in the maze using the dimension of the maze.
        Parameters:
        g - graphics provided by the GUI
        offset - starting point of the GUI and represents the dimensions of the room
